100 g Diced Bacon
1 Cucumber
1 packet Basmati Rice
1 Baby Broccoli
1 Spring Onion
1 Asian Greens
1 packet Sweet Soy Seasoning
200 g Peeled Prawns
2 Garlic
1 drizzle olive oil
¼ cup vinegar (rice wine or white wine)
1 piece egg
½ tsp brown sugar
1 tsp sesame oil
2 tsp soy sauce

• Boil the kettle. Half-fill a medium saucepan with boiling water.
• Add basmati rice and a pinch of salt and cook, uncovered, over high heat until tender, 10 minutes.
• Drain rice, rinse with warm water and set aside.
TIP: The rice will finish cooking in step 4!

• Meanwhile, finely chop garlic. Thinly slice spring onion. Slice cucumber into rounds. Trim Asian greens. Halve any thicker stalks of baby broccoli (see ingredients) lengthways.
• Drain and pat dry peeled prawns. In a medium bowl, combine prawns with a drizzle of olive oil, half the garlic and pepper. Set aside.
• In a second medium bowl, combine the vinegar and a good pinch of sugar and salt.
• Add cucumber to the pickling liquid with just enough water to cover the cucumber. Set aside.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook baby broccoli, tossing, until just tender, 3-4 minutes. Add Asian greens and cook until just wilted, 1-2 minutes.
• Add the remaining garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute. Season to taste.
• Transfer to a plate and cover to keep warm.

• Wipe out frying pan, then return to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook diced bacon, breaking up with a spoon, until golden, 2-3 minutes.
• Push bacon to the side, crack the egg into the pan and scramble until cooked through, 1 minute.
• Add spring onion and sweet soy seasoning and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add the brown sugar, sesame oil and soy sauce. Cook until slightly reduced, 2-3 minutes.
• Add the cooked rice and cook, stirring, until well combined, 2-3 minutes.

• Meanwhile, heat a second large frying pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• When oil is hot, cook prawns, tossing, until pink and starting to curl up, 3-4 minutes.
• Transfer to a plate.

• Drain pickled cucumber.
• Divide bacon fried rice between bowls.
• Top with garlic prawns, sautéed greens and quick-pickled cucumber to serve. Enjoy!